fields.title: Goodbye Mazrigos
fields.body_html:
So after many years we are leaving Mazrigos to pursue new opportunities on Draenor.

It was a hard decision to make and we will be leaveing some of our friends behind, but it was a neccesary step to make in order to get fresh blood and keep the guild going.

Best of luck to everybody staying behind, for everybody else the migration deadline is Sunday 10.5.2015. See you on the other side.

fields.title: Oregorger mythic down!
fields.body_html:
A week after we started raiding together, three raids into our new future, after a few hours of getting used to eachothers and a new style or raiding, Oregorger got killed in mythic!

With victory rushing in our blood we headed for Beastlord Darmac and got him down quickly too. This was a good day to raid. We are proud of how the group has come together and what we see we are progressively doing better.

This is just the start.

fields.title: 3/10M Gruul mythic murdered!
fields.body_html:
After killing lag we figured out it was time to kill the boss too. Then Oregorger. And Beastlord Darmac.

Two full days for Arnold&Meinhard. Will be fun.

Thanks to all the ppl who participated in today's raid. Let's turn up the progressknob now that we are motivated for it. We need some extra juice to kill the next bosses.

fields.title: 6/10M Kromog down!
fields.body_html:
YES!

That was an awesome ending of this raid tier!

First boss where numbers actually matter. Now we know we have what it takes to go further, although we don't have time to do anything more in BrF. Let's use this and "always improve" in Hellfire Citadel so we can get further and in time. That we started (uber) late with progressing in mythic BrF wasn't our fault. So let's take this chance to do it from start of HfC.

Oh, and Butcher and Tectus says hi.

Since we are eventually gonna start doing Mythic (when we get a cupple more people on board). Im gonna link some video guides for the first few boses.

Now Oregorger is probably the easiest of the mythic bosses and is basicly unchanged from heroic. There are 2 different ways of doing phase 2. One is more controled with the raid spliting in two and oregorger always going down a preset path the other is more free for all like the heroic tactic we use but its really more of a personal preference wich one to use. The other change is that we now require 5 interupters for his blackrock barrage sicne he now casts it really fast and each failed interupt means he goes into phase 2 sooner wich is bad.

Option 1: First of the free for all tactic. The raid basicly just stands in the middle section so its really easy to avoid his rolls and we only kill the boxes on the sides when hes far away from that area. You can see that tactic in the video below

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=D7HPFu8wyxk

Option 2: The other Tactic is the controled phase 2 with 2 groups wich can be seen in the video below

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=J_N7grPEMRI

fields.body_html:
Some of the /wa stuff I have floating around:
Can add more later or even create something on request.



First:
Download WeakAuras2 here.
Quick and dirty how-to-guide (can stop reading after "import" ).

How to resize and move imported stuff.

How to deactivate something you have copied or imported:
http://www.vinlacvicek.com/forum/post/253/





Auras ready for import:

Oregorger - Blackrock Barrage - Interrupt warning on correct stack+cast
Helps you reminding when you should interrupt Blackrock Barrage.

Oregorger has 5 stacks of Blackrock Spines.
He removes 1 then starts to cast it on us.
It means if you're 1st to interrupt you are interrupting when he has 4 stacks.
If you're 4th to interrupt you do it when he has 1 stack.
If you're 5th (last) to interrupt you do it when he has zero stacks left (when he has spent his whole buff, and the buff is gone).

In WA you set stack count = 4 if you're first to interrupt.
If you're last you deselect/disable the stack count line and select/enable inverse on the bottom.
Click to see example picture.

In short:
1st interrupt: stack count = 4
2nd interrupt: stack count = 3
3rd interrupt: stack count = 2
4th interrupt: stack count = 1
5th interrupt: disable stack count, enable inverse





0. Auto-delete specific items (no delete confirmation)
Have you ever been tired of manually deleting those shitty items when mining in the garrison?

0. CombatLogging (change when&where in custom trigger1)
Auto-enables combatlogging when you are in raid + Blackrock Foundry + difficulty lvl is normal/heroic/mythic. It even reenables if you travel to Washington DC. Auto-disables combatlogging when you leave raid or any other criterias aren't met.

0. Readycheck = DeathNote:Reset
If you're one of those who use /dn and get confused when it shows deaths from multiple tries.

0. Trade chat spam
Trade/general/lfg chat is so spammy on high pop servers you can't even read /g or /ra before it's gone (if you ever saw something was written). Make a new chat window for trade+general+lfg so you can go there if you wanna read that crap. You can add/remove servers in the custom trigger.

1. In raid and in g1-4 (Enter HfC) (Mythic)
1. In raid but NOT in g1-4 (Exit HfC, you're on STANDBY) (Mythic)
If we happen to be too many for mythic some of us will be on standby but maybe still in the raid. Those ppl are then moved to group 5++. This will tell you if you have to HS out or get in without the raid leader telling you to. (This is usually more relevant on farm when we switch per boss because of targetted looting.)

2. Combat time - timer
Timer addon made inside WeakAuras (you have to /reload UI to enable it, same if you choose load:never).
Can add/subtract time with scrollwheel or mousebuttons, make it start at zero or predetermined time, counting up or down, even start automatically upon entering combat.
Left mouse button on border for moving, right mouse button on border for resizing. Click the red/green button at bottom right for lock/unlock move/resize.
I should probably add a way to hide it by command or minimize it. Some day in the future…

Battle res request
Have you ever died and not noticed you got battle ressed because the window+text is just too similar to when you're dead? This will wake you up (airhorn).

Blackrock Foundry - Debuffs and warnings
Grouped up. You might have copied parts of it already -> delete.

ExternalCDs
(Copied from here.)
Track the dmg red cds that others can give you (as tank).

Helpful raid buffs from others (HRB)
All major raidwide cooldowns with sound on what is more important (fox+roar+devo), so you can move while casting when the hunter use Fox too late. Shows the name of who cast it.

Highmaul - Debuffs and warnings

RaidCDs
(I think it's copied from the same place as ExternalCDs. Just got it from Wildpreacher.)
Shows who have which healing cooldowns, and if they are ready to be abused or what the cooldown duration is.

Readycheck, summon, LFG/LFD/LFR proposal/invite/queue pop, invite request by others
Invites and ready checks can easily be missed when you are alt+tab'ing. Airhorn might wake you up.

Tank: Defensive cooldowns (TDC)
Single target cooldowns others put on you the tank.
With name of the casters and amount of absorb.



Leg ring and trinkets etc:

Legendary ring proc
The progress bar for when the buff is up.
Legendary ring proc - time since last proc
When the ring procs this number counts down from ICD (55s) to zero seconds with white text.
Legendary ring proc - time since last proc - past ICD
When the white number has reached zero it goes away, and this red number starts counting upwards with red text (until the ring procs again). Higher red number means increasingly higher chance for the ring to proc very soon (TM). On fights less than 6 mins you want to track as many of these ICDs as possible, so you can delay the use of the 3 min dps cd for when you have multiple procs up at the same time (or they are coming very soon). (Still: don't fool yourself on 7 min fights.)

Trinket - Darmac's Unstable Talisman
Trinket - Shards of Nothing
Trinket - Blackiron Micro Crucible

Lava Burst cast time
Now that we have all these haste buffs that come on use or with ICD there is a high chance we will get less than 1s cast time for our spammy spell. This tracks the cast time. Change the spell name in the custom display.


Edit:
8/5
Added "Oregorger - Blackrock Barrage - Interrupt warning on correct stack+cast".

11/5
"Combat time - timer": Fixed it once and for all. Will now load and do and save the char profiles correctly.

30/6
Added "RaidCDs".
Switched out "1. In raid and in g1-4 (Enter Blackrock Foundry) (Mythic)" with HfC.
Same with the "NOT in g1-4".
Sorted all the auras alphabetically.

fields.body:
[size]Some of the /wa stuff I have floating around:[/size]
Can add more later or even create something on request.



[b][u]First:[/u][/b]
[url=http://www.curse.com/addons/wow/weakauras-2]Download WeakAuras2 here.[/url]
[url=http://www.icy-veins.com/forums/topic/8128-weakauras-fast-start/]Quick and dirty how-to-guide (can stop reading after "import" ).[/url]

[url=http://sunniersartofwar.com/blog/2014/07/08/how-to-change-the-size-and-positioning-of-a-weak-aura/]How to resize and move imported stuff.[/url]

How to deactivate something you have copied or imported:
[url=http://www.vinlacvicek.com/forum/post/253/]http://www.vinlacvicek.com/forum/post/253/[/url]





[b][u]Auras ready for import:[/u][/b]

[url=http://pastebin.com/PrCmAZ7f]Oregorger - Blackrock Barrage - Interrupt warning on correct stack+cast[/url]
Helps you reminding when you should interrupt Blackrock Barrage.

Oregorger has 5 stacks of Blackrock Spines.
He removes 1 then starts to cast it on us.
It means if you're 1st to interrupt you are interrupting when he has 4 stacks.
If you're 4th to interrupt you do it when he has 1 stack.
If you're 5th (last) to interrupt you do it when he has zero stacks left (when he has spent his whole buff, and the buff is gone).

In WA you set stack count = 4 if you're first to interrupt.
If you're last you deselect/disable the stack count line and select/enable inverse on the bottom.
[url=http://imgur.com/MzTu0Es]Click to see example picture.[/url]

In short:
1st interrupt: stack count = 4
2nd interrupt: stack count = 3
3rd interrupt: stack count = 2
4th interrupt: stack count = 1
5th interrupt: disable stack count, enable inverse





[url=http://pastebin.com/uSESgmWf]0. Auto-delete specific items (no delete confirmation)[/url]
Have you ever been tired of manually deleting those shitty items when mining in the garrison?

[url=http://pastebin.com/ir8bLMcF]0. CombatLogging (change when&where in custom trigger1)[/url]
Auto-enables combatlogging when you are in raid + Blackrock Foundry + difficulty lvl is normal/heroic/mythic. It even reenables if you travel to Washington DC. Auto-disables combatlogging when you leave raid or any other criterias aren't met.

[url=http://pastebin.com/7fZ2Lrvn]0. Readycheck = DeathNote:Reset[/url]
If you're one of those who use /dn and get confused when it shows deaths from multiple tries.

[url=http://pastebin.com/jrxpRBh4]0. Trade chat spam[/url]
Trade/general/lfg chat is so spammy on high pop servers you can't even read /g or /ra before it's gone (if you ever saw something was written). Make a new chat window for trade+general+lfg so you can go there if you wanna read that crap. You can add/remove servers in the custom trigger.

[url=http://pastebin.com/92dF9CK7]1. In raid and in g1-4 (Enter HfC) (Mythic)[/url]
[url=http://pastebin.com/mWCs2AMy]1. In raid but NOT in g1-4 (Exit HfC, you're on STANDBY) (Mythic)[/url]
If we happen to be too many for mythic some of us will be on standby but maybe still in the raid. Those ppl are then moved to group 5++. This will tell you if you have to HS out or get in without the raid leader telling you to. (This is usually more relevant on farm when we switch per boss because of targetted looting.)

[url=http://pastebin.com/a0N0n7sY]2. Combat time - timer[/url]
Timer addon made inside WeakAuras (you have to /reload UI to enable it, same if you choose load:never).
Can add/subtract time with scrollwheel or mousebuttons, make it start at zero or predetermined time, counting up or down, even start automatically upon entering combat.
Left mouse button on border for moving, right mouse button on border for resizing. Click the red/green button at bottom right for lock/unlock move/resize.
I should probably add a way to hide it by command or minimize it. Some day in the future...

[url=http://pastebin.com/pDZfiGcu]Battle res request[/url]
Have you ever died and not noticed you got battle ressed because the window+text is just too similar to when you're dead? This will wake you up (airhorn).

[url=http://pastebin.com/Z5P0PBtW]Blackrock Foundry - Debuffs and warnings[/url]
Grouped up. You might have copied parts of it already -> delete.

[url=http://pastebin.com/2rPKF0Tt]ExternalCDs[/url]
(Copied from [url=http://www.reddit.com/r/wow/comments/2xaww4/i_created_a_weakaura_to_track_raid_cooldowns_and/]here[/url].)
Track the dmg red cds that others can give you (as tank).

[url=http://pastebin.com/avw9XfVc]Helpful raid buffs from others (HRB)[/url]
All major raidwide cooldowns with sound on what is more important (fox+roar+devo), so you can move while casting when the hunter use Fox too late. Shows the name of who cast it.

[url=http://pastebin.com/cTduZGC9]Highmaul - Debuffs and warnings[/url]

[url=http://pastebin.com/u10J9MDR]RaidCDs[/url]
(I think it's copied from the same place as ExternalCDs. Just got it from Wildpreacher.)
Shows who have which healing cooldowns, and if they are ready to be abused or what the cooldown duration is.

[url=http://pastebin.com/qxYxJVKa]Readycheck, summon, LFG/LFD/LFR proposal/invite/queue pop, invite request by others[/url]
Invites and ready checks can easily be missed when you are alt+tab'ing. Airhorn might wake you up.

[url=http://pastebin.com/khb0WWhs]Tank: Defensive cooldowns (TDC)[/url]
Single target cooldowns others put on you the tank.
With name of the casters and amount of absorb.



[b][u]Leg ring and trinkets etc:[/u][/b]

[url=http://pastebin.com/1b7ZTSwu]Legendary ring proc[/url]
The progress bar for when the buff is up.
[url=http://pastebin.com/awgKunZv]Legendary ring proc - time since last proc[/url]
When the ring procs this number counts down from ICD (55s) to zero seconds with white text.
[url=http://pastebin.com/M26L4cWz]Legendary ring proc - time since last proc - past ICD[/url]
When the white number has reached zero it goes away, and this red number starts counting upwards with red text (until the ring procs again). Higher red number means increasingly higher chance for the ring to proc very soon (TM). On fights less than 6 mins you want to track as many of these ICDs as possible, so you can delay the use of the 3 min dps cd for when you have multiple procs up at the same time (or they are coming very soon). (Still: don't fool yourself on 7 min fights.)

[url=http://pastebin.com/tKYU0s2e]Trinket - Darmac's Unstable Talisman[/url]
[url=http://pastebin.com/GpTkdBe7]Trinket - Shards of Nothing[/url]
[url=http://pastebin.com/d2n8z0wn]Trinket - Blackiron Micro Crucible[/url]

[url=http://pastebin.com/KT2wSU4y]Lava Burst cast time[/url]
Now that we have all these haste buffs that come on use or with ICD there is a high chance we will get less than 1s cast time for our spammy spell. This tracks the cast time. Change the spell name in the custom display.


[b][u]Edit:[/u][/b]
8/5
Added "Oregorger - Blackrock Barrage - Interrupt warning on correct stack+cast".

11/5
"Combat time - timer": Fixed it once and for all. Will now load and do and save the char profiles correctly.

30/6
Added "RaidCDs".
Switched out "1. In raid and in g1-4 (Enter [u]Blackrock Foundry[/u]) (Mythic)" with [u]HfC[/u].
Same with the "NOT in g1-4".
Sorted all the auras alphabetically.

fields.body_html:
We have created a new guild on Draenor today with the same name as on Mazrigos. The old one will stay untouched where it is. When we need/want to show off our old achievements we can point over to Mazrigos.

This also means you can come earlier if you want. Rapiu+Frost+Bishi have chars in the new Draenor guild.





Before transfering:

For you personally when you transfer your char you will bring everything over. Everything in your bank, bags and voidstorage. Your mailbox and auction house(s) have to be empty though. You'll get an error if there is something in them.

Max gold you can bring over with your char is 50 000 g. There are several tricks to move more "gold" over, but I don't wanna write anything official here in case Blizz have fixed it or removed some options. Ask around in the guild and ask others for confirmation if you'd like. But for the old ways to move gold over is Vial of the sands' or moving a guild over by yourself.

If you choose to move a guild over you must keep in mind that you have to be guild master for 7 days on the char you want to move before the system even starts to think about it. But then the gold cap is … gold cap: 1 mill gold minus 1 b.

Remember to move crafting mats, flasks, pots and other shit you want with you from your alts to your transfer char.


Char transfer = 20 euro
GM+gbank transfer = 30 euro





After transferring:

All addons will now think that you have created a new char on a new server. If an addon use profiles the profile will now be empty.

For all other addons you can trick them by copy a folder:

Open fileexplorer to:
    \World of Warcraft\WTF\Account\%accountname%\Mazrigos\%yourcharname%
copy everything there and paste them in:
    Draenor\%stillthesamecharname%

The macros are saved on the server and refuse to read from the local file. Instead of trying to force WoW to read the the macro file you can rather:
  1. Open:
    2. \World of Warcraft\WTF\Account\%accountname%\Mazrigos\%yourcharname%\macros-cache.txt
  2. Log in to your char.
  3. Create a new macro.
  4. Copy the macro text from Notepad and paste in the WoW macro.
  5. Repeat for all macros.


Example from Notepad:
VER 3 0100000000000002 "Capacitor totem" "INV_Misc_QuestionMark"
#showtooltip capacitor totem
/cast [mod:ctrl] totemic projection
/cast capacitor totem
END

Copy the 3 lines;
#showtooltip capacitor totem
/cast [mod:ctrl] totemic projection
/cast capacitor totem

Paste them in the WoW macro.


The account wide macros are untouched.


Addons that use profiles usually set the profile for each char as charname-servername. It means that your old profiles are named yourcharname-Mazrigos. When you have moved to the new server you can copy the profiles over to yourcharname-Draenor.

For addons like AllPlayed you might have to delete or ignore the Mazrigos char.

If you use TradeSkillMaster to easier mail shit around you have to check your mailto chars, ignore chars and ignore server settings.

Weakauras doesn't operate with servers (realm) unless you manually pick them under Load or write in custom trigger/display.

ElvUI doesn't save all settings in the profile; like bag+skin+unit settings.

Although I am not part of the raiding team, I am also not too content with what's going on on our server.

I still have to do my research on what migrating to a more populated server brings me. Will I be able to send stuff from my alt character on Mazrigos to Draenor? And is there a seperate auction house? Gotta check Draenor itself out.

So if I get it right, for 20€, all I can transfer is one character, right? There's no way to like buy a package to transfer more characters for a lower price? xD


All in all, I think I' be ready to move to Draenor with you, provided I can keep my social spot in the guild. I can safely say the same for Sanyoor. Perhaps I'll even join the raiding team, but that's gonna be when school's out for summer. Provided the raiding times would be normal, I'd be happy to join the team with my pally. He'll probably be around 680 by then anyway, so there'll only be a small step to make. Also, same for Sanyoor.

So if I get it right, for 20€, all I can transfer is one character, right? There's no way to like buy a package to transfer more characters for a lower price? xD


All in all, I think I' be ready to move to Draenor with you, provided I can keep my social spot in the guild. I can safely say the same for Sanyoor. Perhaps I'll even join the raiding team, but that's gonna be when school's out for summer. Provided the raiding times would be normal, I'd be happy to join the team with my pally. He'll probably be around 680 by then anyway, so there'll only be a small step to make. Also, same for Sanyoor.

fields.body_html:
Can only mail heirlooms between servers, although it isn't needed now with the heirloom window.

There is 1 auction house for each server or connected servers (like Mazrigos+Lightbringer).

20 euro for 1 char. No package deal.

And yes, you can keep your social spot. More ppl = more fun, no matter which rank they are in.

Draenor also opens up for many more options that we can't even dream about on Mazrigos. Big servers truly go by
more ppl = more fun

Didn't notice one thing before and that is that Draenor is also a PVP server. Since I remember how brilliant world pvp was on Daggerspine while it was still alive, I kind of wish to also get that in the package. Therefore, I might also consider an option of migrating to another server. If so, our paths will split. I must say I am not too happy about it, as I happened to make some good buddies I ocassionally talk to in the guild and because everyone seemed to be quite helpful, but still there are two minuses to it.

If I happen to move to a pvp server, does anyone know of a decent Slo-only horde guild on a high pop pvp server? I know it's kind of a dream, but…

fields.body_html:
I just transferred an alt from Kazzak to Draenor and I can confirm that buying garrison blueprints and heirloom upgrades on Kazzak and then sell them back to the same vendor on Draenor works. AND you don't lose any money. You get back 100% of the purchase value.


Blueprints lvl 3 cost 1000g but are UNIQUE. So can't fill your bags+bank with 1 type.

Timeworn heirloom scabbard costs 5000g and you can buy as many as you want. Only drawback is they don't stack, so 1 bagslot = 1 item = 5000g. But if you clean up your bank+bags and have 50 slots free you can transport 250 000g this way + the 50 000g gold coin limit.

fields.body_html:
More UI settings to check:

Blizz orig settings.
Worth mentioning:

Controls -> auto luut

Combat -> (dont) show spell alerts

Raid profiles -> select all, then delesect "horizontal groups", "display pets", "display border", "display only dispellable buffs"

(Don't forget to check ElvUI UnitFrames and deselect "party frames" and "raid frames", and go to unitframes -> tank frames and disable it.)

Camera -> max camera distance = far

and use a macro like this to get even further camera distance:

/script SetCVar ("cameraDistancemaxFactor" ,1)
/script SetCVar ("cameraDistancemax" ,50)

fields.body_html:
Greetings!

You have chosen to apply to Vin la Cvicek and have been /ginvited and accepted for trial. Before we go on and raid together there is something we want you to read and do first.



A short resume of our history can be found here:
http://www.wowprogress.com/guild/eu/draenor/Vin+la+Cvicek





Your expectations to us

By accepting this /ginvite you have also accepted the following rules and statements:

Raiding with us is optional. There is no rule in the universe that says you HAVE TO raid with us. You are here because you want to.

But since we are a group of real people who spend real time and real energy on this we need some rules so this group effort goes more smoothly. If we don't live up to your expectations you are free to leave at any moment, even if passed trial. It's your choice.

The calendar is filled with future raids. Since we all like to plan ahead of time we accept or decline to what our schedule looks like. Having to decline a raid day happens. We all got some special events some times a year. If you find your IRL time doesn't strerch far enough to come raid for a certain day or week you decline the calendar events and tell the officers for how long. If you later find out this has to become permanent we have a slacker rank for just this purpose.

You can still be in the guild without having to raid. It's optional after all.



Our expectations to you

We recently migrated to this server to have an easier time recruiting and then finally get the progression we have planned for so long. We have done big changes within the guild to push us further towards our goal, and we will continue to make changes when we see they will give us an advantage. Now with recruitment we have lots of new ppl, and we all have to adjust to eachothers.

So as you can see there is lots happening at once. We are in essence recreating the guild but without losing our old values.

Because of this the guild will be changing and progressing in another rate in 2 months than it does today. What you see today won't be the case in the future. We will be constantly improving and trying out different ppl to see who fits progression better. How fast and how far we will get depends on what each of us are doing, and how hard each of us are pushing. If we happen to invite some lower performing persons to the raid it's done to give them experience as possible future raiders, make sure we are enough for the 20 person limit for mythic, and to get more looted items out of the bosses who die in heroic mode. They are here to help us out for as long as it can be justified. It's important that everybody perform their very best at all times so we can get the bosses down smootly even with a variety of players.

This is where you come into the picture.

When we are close to downing a new mythic boss there is so little extra that is needed from it to go from a wipe to a kill. If we wipe a whole day on a boss the officers then sit down and analyze what went wrong and what can be done better. If you happen to not do your best because "that other guy is slacking so I won't bother to push my max either" it will look to us as you are a slacker too. We will end up replacing two instead of one.

Same goes for when we have farmed a tier for weeks and months and then get a new raid tier on our hands. We will pick those we know will perform well and consistently. Rest will get some fun too, but they have to wait until the bosses are on farm mode.

Anyone who makes drama will get the same treatment, but they might get it faster or even demoted. We do not want any kind of drama in this guild. Not even lootwhoring drama! We are gearing up the group so the group can progress further faster, and that means some will get more gear faster than others.

The officers have a set rulebook for who gets loot in which order. If you don't agree you might not fit in with us.


Some last points:
  • Don't die > do everything right > good numbers >>>>> bad numbers
  • Perform average or better compared to the raid group to keep your raid spot, and continue to find ways to improve.
  • If there are more of your class+spec in the guild then only the best will be picked.
  • Class stacking might happen too.
  • We can help you out if you ask, but we can't help if you don't know what to ask for.
  • Treat the in-game calendar as your IRL work schedule. The consequences are the same.
  • Same goes for how you treat others.
  • Ask on TeamSpeak/Mumble if you need info/refreshment on specific fight elements.
  • If each and every one of us give a little extra to the group the group will grow pretty fast.
  • DPS-whoring on wrong targets at crucial moments will result in a kick if you don't improve. If you whore like that you single-handedly wipe the group. All by yourself. Gz on that achievement!
  • If you disagree with some decisions during raids you still do what you are told to. We can discuss it later if we are in combat. Maybe we were wrong. Maybe you were wrong. But for this group to function we need all to do their jobs, couse it's almost impossible to analyze what went wrong if everybody did what they randomly wanted to.
  • This guild care about solutions. All problems and "problems" will be solved in one way or the other. Or the third.



Raiding days+hours

Monday
Wednesday
Thursday.

1900-2230.

Be online on the correct character ready for invite and at the instance portal 10 minutes before the calendar says the raid will start. We will start clearing trash immediately.

We might do alt+social+trial run on some sundays.



Mandatory addons

Curse Client
Update all your addons before raid.
Makes it easier for all of us.


CalendarNotify
CalendarNotify pops up a window every time a new calendar event invite has been created. It also gives a reminder about today's events when you log in (and /reload). Missing calendar invites with this addon is impossible.


RCLootCouncil
RCLootCouncilmakes lootdistribution 100x more easy for both the masterlooter+lootcouncil+those who want loot. You can only get loot from main raids through this addon.

No addon = no loot.


WeakAuras 2
What we require through WeakAuras is to copy our raid boss warnings and other raid tools. Building help for other spell and cooldown is option, although we highly encourage it since it can give anywhere between 10-50% dps increase.

If you haven't used WA before and want to try build helping tools we suggest you watch some basic guides first and try recreate what they showed there. After that try google/twitch up some solutions you might wanna try out. Then we can start become helpful, since now you are more aware about what you want.


BigWigs Bossmods
Earlier there was only DBM. Now it's only BW, but somehow DBM is still around in some ppl's UI folder. BW is far superior in all ways, and the raid leaders get a much easier time when using it. But if someone use DBM there will always be compability problems around patch and upgrade days, and the raid as a whole wastes lots of time every time the DBM'ers have to fiddle with it.

On top of this: BW is used by all top guilds and every guild who are trying to do mythic the right way. This means BW always is updated within hours after a hotfix is deployed. DBM has a very shady history on this, where it has taken them 3 weeks to just add a simple planned patch. And this wasn't a single case only…

Optional:
http://www.curse.com/addons/wow/bigwigs_voice
Same as VEM.
You don't have to configure anything. It adds itself to all the bosses. But there might be some boss abilities you want to remove sound warning for so you don't get totally spammed down, like Socretar's Exert Dominance if you aren't an interrupter.


Hansgar And Franzok Assist
Simplifies searing plate, stamper and smart stamper dodging so much it's almost cheating.
Watch this video for setting it up:
Hans'gar & Franzok Mythic | Using an addon to survive the stamp phase as ranged. - YouTube


Exorsus Raid Tools
It shows which hand is yours in the Kromog handphase.



Mandatory WAs

Instance dependant. Ask for links in raid chat to easily copy/import them.

You can also find something useful here:
http://www.vinlacvicek.com/forum/topic/36/



Preparation for new bosses

When you prepare for new bosses in a new raid tier you save yourself and the raid for 1h of trial and error and wiping. If you don't prepare for a new boss you will make the whole raid lagg 1h behind. Everybody will remember you for being the one who screwed up the most.

When you find a certain part of a boss encounter you die repeatedly on, and you end up being alone of doing it or one of the few, you should do that boss over and over in LFR+normal mode until you get it right. Experience makes you improve. Dead dps do no dps. And needing a personal healer is 2 raid spots wasted. Abuse WeakAuras to get past these boss abilities faster.

FatBossTV makes good video guides:
youtube.com/user/FatbossTV

2 minute guides (videos get uploaded slower):
https://www.youtube.com/user/losgamingshow/videos

One page picture guide (whoever is making them):
http://imgur.com/a/N2IP5



Communication

Only english and piratespeak in guild chat, raid chat and raid channel on TeamSpeak/Mumble. We even accept weird and bad accents.

Healers:
/join VLCheal


For raids we use TeamSpeak3 and microphones.
http://www.teamspeak.com/?page=downloads
85.236.109.225:10187

TeamSpeak doesn't auto-adjust ppl's microphones like Mumble does. If someone has low volume you can right click their name in TS, choose "Change Volume" and move the bar to +5 to +10 dB depending on their volume. One person might even need +15 dB, while another might need -5 dB.


We also have Mumble as backup.
http://www.mumble.com/mumble-download.php
sky.siol.net
64646

Set up both TS and Mumble just in case, and calibrate microphone in both.



Consumables

Healing tonic.
Do NOT ask for healthstones. It won't heal enough on mythic.

Only best flask, best food and augment runes on progress bosses we are done training on. 2% wipes can be avoided that way.



Calendar

You already use the CalendarNotify addon and get notified when the officers create new calendar events which you get invited to.

Always answer all of them, and do it asap. The addon will continue to remind you every time you log in and reload UI until you have. If you are unsure for all raids 2 months into the future you can accept them all and change to decline when you know you won't make it. Tentative is awesome for personal use, but for the raid leader it means the same as decline. Never use tentative to hint that you are coming. Talk to the raid leader or officers instead.

You can also reply to this thread outside the game about your planned AFK:
http://www.vinlacvicek.com/forum/topic/43/

The raid leader needs to plan who to take for each raid, and also in well time before the actual raid day. If you accepted but didn't show up, and also didn't tell the officers in another way, you eventually end up in the unreliable bin.



Breaks, afk and brb during raids

We will have one 5 min break when we have raided for about 1,5h and one 10 min break about 1h later.

If you need an emergency brb for bathroom or similar do your best to do it right after the boss is dead so you are back with spare time before we start on the next boss.

And remember: it's called emergency. A person who is slacking after bosses is wasting time and energy for the rest of the group, and we will eventually have to replace that person so it won't demoralize the group.



Looting

Looting can be done across the whole raid instance. There is absolutely no reason to wait at the dead boss for the loot.

Click the correct loot option in the RCLootCouncil window that pops up and start clear the trash.

If you happen to get an item on bonus roll after you clicked an upgrade option for the same item that dropped from the boss, /w the loot master (usually Rapiu) to disregard your upgrade click. Same if you change your mind right after you clicked options.

Having enchants and gems ready in your bags to immediately use the new item is a massive plus, and doesn't even cost you extra money since it will be used soon anyways.



Loot distribution

Main-spec > important off-specs > trials > alts > off-spec > transmog
DPS > healers > tanks

We distribute after what the guild and raid group will benefit the most from. There are many parameters involved, but in short we give more and earlier to those who perform best in the group. All will get loot, but those who can get more out of each stat will help the group more, and then make sure the rest will get loot faster too.



Streaming while raiding

Mute TeamSpeak/Mumble.
Hide guild chat.
Hide raid chat.



/w'ing officers during raids

We encourage everybody to think critically and constructively. We also welcome good suggestions.

During raids there is lots going on in the background that the members don't see or hear. The raid leader(s) can be extremely busy throughout the whole raid duration, and might not have time to /w about all and everything. One of the raid leader's main tasks is to make sure the raid goes as efficient as possible, so if you have good and important suggestions you can go on and /w. Otherwise try ask one of the other officers or wait until after raid. We can always do a fast meeting after raid with you and all the officers and listen to what you have to say, analyze, dissect, conclude, find a solution, and set it to life swiftly if it would work.

If you have some good ideas on new bosses we can discuss them on TS/Mumble when the first boss tries have calmed down.





Very short summary

All that is written here is something we all have been complaining about throughout our years of raiding.

We now write these as "rules" and "employment contract" so that we can finally get rid of those annoying issues.

For all who are raiding with their common sense intact are already covering most, if not all, that is written here.

All guilds who are trying to do serious raiding have all the same rules, but they aren't that often written down, and often lead to confusion about what is expected. We want to be more open and direct about what we want and have less unspoken rules that can be randomly broken, and you will have less to worry about.


We care very much for you all no matter what we ask for or what you say! We all just express it in different ways.

fields.body:
[b]Greetings![/b]

You have chosen to apply to Vin la Cvicek and have been /ginvited and accepted for trial. Before we go on and raid together there is something we want you to read and do first.



A short resume of our history can be found here:
[url=http://www.wowprogress.com/guild/eu/draenor/Vin+la+Cvicek]http://www.wowprogress.com/guild/eu/draenor/Vin+la+Cvicek[/url]





[b][size=6]Your expectations to us[/size][/b]

By accepting this /ginvite you have also accepted the following rules and statements:

Raiding with us is optional. There is no rule in the universe that says you HAVE TO raid with us. You are here because you want to.

But since we are a group of real people who spend real time and real energy on this we need some rules so this group effort goes more smoothly. If we don't live up to your expectations you are free to leave at any moment, even if passed trial. It's your choice.

The calendar is filled with future raids. Since we all like to plan ahead of time we accept or decline to what our schedule looks like. Having to decline a raid day happens. We all got some special events some times a year. If you find your IRL time doesn't strerch far enough to come raid for a certain day or week you decline the calendar events and tell the officers for how long. If you later find out this has to become permanent we have a slacker rank for just this purpose. 

You can still be in the guild without having to raid. It's optional after all.



[b][size=6]Our expectations to you[/size][/b]

We recently migrated to this server to have an easier time recruiting and then finally get the progression we have planned for so long. We have done big changes within the guild to push us further towards our goal, and we will continue to make changes when we see they will give us an advantage. Now with recruitment we have lots of new ppl, and we all have to adjust to eachothers.

So as you can see there is lots happening at once. We are in essence recreating the guild but without losing our old values.

Because of this the guild will be changing and progressing in another rate in 2 months than it does today. What you see today won't be the case in the future. We will be constantly improving and trying out different ppl to see who fits progression better. How fast and how far we will get depends on what each of us are doing, and how hard each of us are pushing. If we happen to invite some lower performing persons to the raid it's done to give them experience as possible future raiders, make sure we are enough for the 20 person limit for mythic, and to get more looted items out of the bosses who die in heroic mode. They are here to help us out for as long as it can be justified. It's important that everybody perform their very best at all times so we can get the bosses down smootly even with a variety of players.

This is where you come into the picture.

When we are close to downing a new mythic boss there is so little extra that is needed from it to go from a wipe to a kill. If we wipe a whole day on a boss the officers then sit down and analyze what went wrong and what can be done better. If you happen to not do your best because "that other guy is slacking so I won't bother to push my max either" it will look to us as you are a slacker too. We will end up replacing two instead of one.

Same goes for when we have farmed a tier for weeks and months and then get a new raid tier on our hands. We will pick those we know will perform well and consistently. Rest will get some fun too, but they have to wait until the bosses are on farm mode.

Anyone who makes drama will get the same treatment, but they might get it faster or even demoted. We do not want any kind of drama in this guild. Not even lootwhoring drama! We are gearing up the group so the group can progress further faster, and that means some will get more gear faster than others.

The officers have a set rulebook for who gets loot in which order. If you don't agree you might not fit in with us.


Some last points:
[list]
[*] Don't die > do everything right > good numbers >>>>> bad numbers
[*] Perform average or better compared to the raid group to keep your raid spot, and continue to find ways to improve.
[*] If there are more of your class+spec in the guild then only the best will be picked.
[*] Class stacking might happen too.
[*] We can help you out if you ask, but we can't help if you don't know what to ask for.
[*] Treat the in-game calendar as your IRL work schedule. The consequences are the same.
[*] Same goes for how you treat others.
[*] Ask on TeamSpeak/Mumble if you need info/refreshment on specific fight elements.
[*] If each and every one of us give a little extra to the group the group will grow pretty fast.
[*] DPS-whoring on wrong targets at crucial moments will result in a kick if you don't improve. If you whore like that you single-handedly wipe the group. All by yourself. Gz on that achievement!
[*] If you disagree with some decisions during raids you still do what you are told to. We can discuss it later if we are in combat. Maybe we were wrong. Maybe you were wrong. But for this group to function we need all to do their jobs, couse it's almost impossible to analyze what went wrong if everybody did what they randomly wanted to.
[*] This guild care about solutions. All problems and "problems" will be solved in one way or the other. Or the third.
[/list]



[b][size=6]Raiding days+hours[/size][/b]

Monday
Wednesday
Thursday.

1900-2230.

Be online on the correct character ready for invite and at the instance portal 10 minutes before the calendar says the raid will start. We will start clearing trash immediately.

We might do alt+social+trial run on some sundays.



[b][size=6]Mandatory addons[/size][/b]

[url=http://www.curse.com/client]Curse Client[/url]
Update all your addons before raid.
Makes it easier for all of us.


[url=http://www.curse.com/addons/wow/calendarnotify]CalendarNotify[/url]
CalendarNotify pops up a window every time a new calendar event invite has been created. It also gives a reminder about today's events when you log in (and /reload). Missing calendar invites with this addon is impossible.


[url=http://www.curse.com/addons/wow/rclootcouncil]RCLootCouncil[/url]
RCLootCouncilmakes lootdistribution 100x more easy for both the masterlooter+lootcouncil+those who want loot. You can only get loot from main raids through this addon.

No addon = no loot.


[url=http://www.curse.com/addons/wow/weakauras-2]WeakAuras 2[/url]
What we require through WeakAuras is to copy our raid boss warnings and other raid tools. Building help for other spell and cooldown is option, although we highly encourage it since it can give anywhere between 10-50% dps increase.

If you haven't used WA before and want to try build helping tools we suggest you watch some basic guides first and try recreate what they showed there. After that try google/twitch up some solutions you might wanna try out. Then we can start become helpful, since now you are more aware about what you want.


[url=http://www.curse.com/addons/wow/big-wigs]BigWigs Bossmods[/url]
Earlier there was only DBM. Now it's only BW, but somehow DBM is still around in some ppl's UI folder. BW is far superior in all ways, and the raid leaders get a much easier time when using it. But if someone use DBM there will always be compability problems around patch and upgrade days, and the raid as a whole wastes lots of time every time the DBM'ers have to fiddle with it.

On top of this: BW is used by all top guilds and every guild who are trying to do mythic the right way. This means BW always is updated within hours after a hotfix is deployed. DBM has a very shady history on this, where it has taken them 3 weeks to just add a simple planned patch. And this wasn't a single case only...

Optional:
[url=http://www.curse.com/addons/wow/bigwigs_voice]http://www.curse.com/addons/wow/bigwigs_voice[/url]
Same as VEM.
You don't have to configure anything. It adds itself to all the bosses. But there might be some boss abilities you want to remove sound warning for so you don't get totally spammed down, like Socretar's Exert Dominance if you aren't an interrupter.


[url=http://www.curse.com/addons/wow/hansgar_and_franzok_assist]Hansgar And Franzok Assist[/url]
Simplifies searing plate, stamper and smart stamper dodging so much it's almost cheating.
Watch this video for setting it up:
[url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iK4eNi3zr1I&feature=youtu.be&t=20s]Hans'gar & Franzok Mythic | Using an addon to survive the stamp phase as ranged. - YouTube[/url]


[url=http://www.curse.com/addons/wow/exorsus-raid-tools]Exorsus Raid Tools[/url]
It shows which hand is yours in the Kromog handphase.



[b][size=6]Mandatory WAs[/size][/b]

Instance dependant. Ask for links in raid chat to easily copy/import them.

You can also find something useful here:
[url=http://www.vinlacvicek.com/forum/topic/36/]http://www.vinlacvicek.com/forum/topic/36/[/url]



[b][size=6]Preparation for new bosses[/size][/b]

When you prepare for new bosses in a new raid tier you save yourself and the raid for 1h of trial and error and wiping. If you don't prepare for a new boss you will make the whole raid lagg 1h behind. Everybody will remember you for being the one who screwed up the most.

When you find a certain part of a boss encounter you die repeatedly on, and you end up being alone of doing it or one of the few, you should do that boss over and over in LFR+normal mode until you get it right. Experience makes you improve. Dead dps do no dps. And needing a personal healer is 2 raid spots wasted. Abuse WeakAuras to get past these boss abilities faster.

FatBossTV makes good video guides:
[url=youtube.com/user/FatbossTV]youtube.com/user/FatbossTV[/url]

2 minute guides (videos get uploaded slower):
[url=https://www.youtube.com/user/losgamingshow/videos]https://www.youtube.com/user/losgamingshow/videos[/url]

One page picture guide (whoever is making them):
[url=http://imgur.com/a/N2IP5]http://imgur.com/a/N2IP5[/url]



[b][size=6]Communication[/size][/b]

Only english and piratespeak in guild chat, raid chat and raid channel on TeamSpeak/Mumble. We even accept weird and bad accents.

Healers:
/join VLCheal


For raids we use TeamSpeak3 and microphones.
[url=http://www.teamspeak.com/?page=downloads]http://www.teamspeak.com/?page=downloads[/url]
85.236.109.225:10187

TeamSpeak doesn't auto-adjust ppl's microphones like Mumble does. If someone has low volume you can right click their name in TS, choose "Change Volume" and move the bar to +5 to +10 dB depending on their volume. One person might even need +15 dB, while another might need -5 dB.


We also have Mumble as backup.
[url=http://www.mumble.com/mumble-download.php]http://www.mumble.com/mumble-download.php[/url]
sky.siol.net
64646

Set up both TS and Mumble just in case, and calibrate microphone in both.



[b][size=6]Consumables[/size][/b]

Healing tonic.
Do NOT ask for healthstones. It won't heal enough on mythic.

Only best flask, best food and augment runes on progress bosses [i]we are done training on[/i]. 2% wipes can be avoided that way.



[b][size=6]Calendar[/size][/b]

You already use the CalendarNotify addon and get notified when the officers create new calendar events which you get invited to.

Always answer all of them, and do it asap. The addon will continue to remind you every time you log in and reload UI until you have. If you are unsure for all raids 2 months into the future you can accept them all and change to decline when you know you won't make it. Tentative is awesome for personal use, but for the raid leader it means the same as decline. Never use tentative to hint that you are coming. Talk to the raid leader or officers instead.

You can also reply to this thread outside the game about your planned AFK:
[url=http://www.vinlacvicek.com/forum/topic/43/]http://www.vinlacvicek.com/forum/topic/43/[/url]

The raid leader needs to plan who to take for each raid, and also in well time before the actual raid day. If you accepted but didn't show up, and also didn't tell the officers in another way, you eventually end up in the unreliable bin.



[b][size=6]Breaks, afk and brb during raids[/size][/b]

We will have one 5 min break when we have raided for about 1,5h and one 10 min break about 1h later.

If you need an emergency brb for bathroom or similar do your best to do it right after the boss is dead so you are back with spare time before we start on the next boss.

And remember: it's called emergency. A person who is slacking after bosses is wasting time and energy for the rest of the group, and we will eventually have to replace that person so it won't demoralize the group.



[b][size=6]Looting[/size][/b]

Looting can be done across the whole raid instance. There is absolutely no reason to wait at the dead boss for the loot.

Click the correct loot option in the RCLootCouncil window that pops up and start clear the trash.

If you happen to get an item on bonus roll after you clicked an upgrade option for the same item that dropped from the boss, /w the loot master (usually Rapiu) to disregard your upgrade click. Same if you change your mind right after you clicked options.

Having enchants and gems ready in your bags to immediately use the new item is a massive plus, and doesn't even cost you extra money since it will be used soon anyways.



[b][size=6]Loot distribution[/size][/b]

Main-spec > important off-specs > trials > alts > off-spec > transmog
DPS > healers > tanks

We distribute after what the guild and raid group will benefit the most from. There are many parameters involved, but in short we give more and earlier to those who perform best in the group. All will get loot, but those who can get more out of each stat will help the group more, and then make sure the rest will get loot faster too.



[b][size=6]Streaming while raiding[/size][/b]

Mute TeamSpeak/Mumble.
Hide guild chat.
Hide raid chat.



[b][size=6]/w'ing officers during raids[/size][/b]

We encourage everybody to think critically and constructively. We also welcome good suggestions.

During raids there is lots going on in the background that the members don't see or hear. The raid leader(s) can be extremely busy throughout the whole raid duration, and might not have time to /w about all and everything. One of the raid leader's main tasks is to make sure the raid goes as efficient as possible, so if you have good and important suggestions you can go on and /w. Otherwise try ask one of the other officers or wait until after raid. We can always do a fast meeting after raid with you and all the officers and listen to what you have to say, analyze, dissect, conclude, find a solution, and set it to life swiftly if it would work.

If you have some good ideas on new bosses we can discuss them on TS/Mumble when the first boss tries have calmed down.





[b][size=6]Very short summary[/size][/b]

All that is written here is something we all have been complaining about throughout our years of raiding.

We now write these as "rules" and "employment contract" so that we can finally get rid of those annoying issues.

For all who are raiding with their common sense intact are already covering most, if not all, that is written here.

All guilds who are trying to do serious raiding have all the same rules, but they aren't that often written down, and often lead to confusion about what is expected. We want to be more open and direct about what we want and have less unspoken rules that can be randomly broken, and you will have less to worry about.


We care very much for you all no matter what we ask for or what you say! We all just express it in different ways.

fields.body_html:
The thread "Introduction to trials" has been written and reviewed by the officers. It's closer to finished, but before we can call it done we want all the members to review it.



The function with this document is exactly what the title says. All new trials will have to read this and do what it says. But, it won't be counting for ONLY trials.

After we have read through it some times, discussed it, and done some changes, it will eventually be all our new "rulebook" aka "employee contract" aka whatever you wanna call it. So spend some time on it now so we can all agree on it later.

The estiamted time before it goes into effect is around mid june or something like that. At that point this feedback thread will be moved to the officer forum for storage, and the discussion is over, and we will have to boey what we all agreed on.



The reason for doing it like this is because we all have been bothered by most of these issues throughout our raiding career. Now that we have given ourselves a new start on a new server we also have to introduce some improvements. These improvements are made so that we won't waste eachother's time. They will ask for a little extra of your time, unless you are already doing them, but what you alone and us as a group will gain will be massive. It won't be a one-way giving. Remember that there are 19 others who are also giving, so in essence you are receiving 19 times more than you give. You'll notice the change in the group really fast when we all do this together.

We all hate that the negative parts that can happen during raids happen. We all wish they never happened. That's why we wanna spoonfeed new trials right away with what we don't wanna see happen in our guild and in our raids (while we also are not doing it ourselves).

At the same time it shouldn't be a new dictatorship of some sort, so wording has to be chosen with care without losing the meaning of the text.



Reply with whatever you have on your mind.

No opinion is wrong (for you).

Application process:


You have 3 options on how to deliver the application:
  1. Forum post application.
  2. Email application.
  3. Combined /w and TeamSpeak meeting (verbal application).



Before you start write the application remember and keep in mind that the application is our the first impression of you.





If you choose option 1 (forum post):

Create a new thread here:
http://www.vinlacvicek.com/forum/topics/2/

Set the topic to:
"Application: yourname (yourspec yourclass)"

Copy this template
and fill in your info on new lines after the questions.





If you choose option 2 (email):

Copy this template
and fill in your info on new lines after the questions.

Send the application to:
applications@vinlacvicek.com





If you choose option 3 (verbal application):
Contact an officer in-game
or contact applications@vinlacvicek.com
to initiate the process.

or contact [url=mailto:applications@vinlacvicek.com]applications@vinlacvicek.com[/url]
to initiate the process.

fields.body_html:
Our officers have the following focus areas at this moment:



Guild master:
Rapiu

Focus areas:
  • Oversee the officer's work and performance.
  • Ensure they have what they need and the time needed to do it.
  • Responsible for initiating new goals, directions and methods, include all officers (and members in big changes) to find the best solution, and make sure the process goes well, as planned and that we reach our goal.
  • Responsible for all social aspects of the guild.
  • Assist any officer where and when needed.



Raid leader:
Frostmaster

Focus areas:
  • In general all that is raid related in the technical direction.
  • Plan ahead of time and create a strategy on how to proceed with the order and rate of progression in new raid instances.
  • Plan what will be done for each raid day.
  • Efficient raids.
  • Watch the raid during encounters, tell timers, do minor adjustments, etc.
  • Responsible for directing and redirecting raid members on who get spots for each boss and who will do which task during the encounter.
  • Responsible for assessing player skills and if they are adequate as a temporary or pemanent member, and to keep a continued discussion on this topic with the other officers.
  • Cooperate with the healing leader.
  • Tell the recruitment officer which class+spec is needed.



Healing leader:
Bishii

Focus areas:
  • Design and develop http://www.vinlacvicek.com/
  • All related to healing and damage reduction in the techical direction.
  • Plan ahead of time how many healers and which healer classes are needed for each boss.
  • Plan ahead of time which cooldowns are needed where.
  • Responsible for assessing healer player skills and if they are adequate as temporary or permanent member, and to keep a continued discussion on this topic with the other officers.
  • Cooperate with the raid leader.
  • Tell the recruitment officer which healer class+spec is needed.



Recruitment officer:
Dotftw

Focus areas:
  • Draenor relations.
  • Recieve a list of which classes+specs that we need to recruit.
  • Spam trade chat with recruitment macro and redirect possible applicants to the website.
  • Answer forum applications, investigate who the person is and accept for trial if made of the right quality.
  • Guide new trials when they join and through the first raids.



Substitute raid leader:
Knof

Focus areas:
  • Substitute for the raid leader when the raid leader is away.
  • Assist the raid leader and the raid with whatever has to be done.
  • See and take opportunities midfight.



All-arounder:
Gothikanemo






On top of this:
All officers are always discussing changes needed before decisions are made.
They are also helping eachothers during raids, etc, although each officer has the final word on their own area.

About yourself

Name: Sean

Age: 18

Gender: Male

Country: UK
Your computer

System specifications: 8GB RAM (Im not techy so i cant answer much here)

FPS during general raiding: 30-40

FPS during raiding and heavy load (bloodlust+spam everything+shiny boss abilities): 20-25

Do you have and use a microphone? Yes

Internet connection (use speedtest, pick Paris which is where the Draenor server is located, and paste the result-URL):http://www.speedtest.net/my-result/4365286690

How often do you disconnect? Rarely.

How often does your PC crash? Never.
Character information

Character name: Obli

Class: Death Knight

Spec: Blood/Unholy

Amory link: http://eu.battle.net/wow/en/character/draenor/Obli/advanced

Off-spec (if any): Unholy

Alts worth mentioning: 650 Warrior tank
Raiding

Raiding schedule and IRL (will our raiding schedule fit your real life?): I raid with After hours on Silvermoon and they are a late night raiding guild starting at 23:00st so these times interlock perfectly.

Previous expansion experience: Cata - 8/8N 1/8HC, MoP - 13/14HC Pre patch and 14/14M after post patch, WoD - 9/10M

Mindset (describe your attitude on progress and farm raids): During progressing i am focused and my mind is only on what i need to do to make this fight a kill. During farm i am slightly more relaxed but not to the point where we cant kill anything because of it.

Combatlog links: https://www.warcraftlogs.com/rankings/character/3207258/latest/

Screenshot of your UI while raiding (use Imgur):

Which important addons and WAs do you use? I use; Omni CC, Exorsus raid tools, Skada, big wigs and Weakauras.

Which macros do you use? Focus mass gripping

Which keybinds do you use? My naga, 123, shft 123, shft naga buttons.

Explain your talent and glyph choices and alternatives: Whilst in blood my talents generally stay the same unless rolling Breath of Singdragosa in which plague leech, breath and glyph of chains of ice is used.
T1 - Plague leech/UB
T2 - Purgatory
T3 - Deaths Advance
T4 - Blood tap
T5 - Death pact
T6 - Mass grip
T7 - BoS for aoe blood, Necro plague for aoe and defile for blood if boss is still.

How do you check what your dps is like? Skada.

Where do you find new info about your class? Summonstone, a brilliant website ran by Skullflower.

If you have geared alts, at which lvl can you play them? My main is a 701 warrior from Silvermoon called Exeige, i raid the entire BRF Mythic so i know what im doing !

Do you know anyone from the guild? Nope.
Previous guilds
Which guilds and roles? Currently in After Hours on my main and used to be in Boom time on Draenor EU as their warrior dps until the atmosphere became too volatile and i had to leave. Ive been playing dk for five years alongside my warrior.
Anything else you wanna add? Thank you for your time.

Have some patterns for the upcoming boss

fields.body_html:
Good job!



So in short:

Orientation is from down to up (remember the arrow/flying V for pattern 3).

Green only need to switch between 2 tiles.

Blue only needs to switch between 4 tiles, where the 2 left are the most used.



On heroic it's possible to stand on the stationary floor, on the edge opposite side of where the stamp will spawn. I can't remember if that still is the case mythic, but usually it's the same. This means that during this phase where the belts are moving you can mostly just "stand still" and not get bothered by the belts. Just move a few yards to not get directly crushed, or standing too close so you get burned by the sides.

The 2 last of the 4 tiles are for when we get 3 stamps close to eachothers. At this point it is VERY important that we stand close to the edge of a tile so we can run against the belts with time to spare for the next stamping stamps.

I hope my post isn't too poor. If you want any information, come to discuss with me
Finnera

First name: Petrut
Age: 19
Gender:Male
Country:Romania
Your computer

System specifications:i7 3.1hz. 4gb ram, nvidia gt 820m 2gb

FPS during raiding and heavy load (bloodlust+spam everything+shiny boss abilities): idk exactly

Internet connection (use speedtest, pick Paris which is where the Draenor server is located, and paste the result-URL):http://www.speedtest.net/my-result/4398683506
How often do you disconnect? almost never
How often does your PC crash? never
Character information

Character name:Killovolt
Class:Shaman
Spec:Enhancement
Amory link:http://eu.battle.net/wow/en/character/draenor/Killovolt/simple
Off-spec (if any):I can go ele and resto, depending of what is needed, but atm none of these are geared
Alts worth mentioning:i have alts but none are max level since i focus on my shaman
Raiding

Raiding schedule and IRL (will our raiding schedule fit your real life?):yes
Previous expansion experience:8/8 hc dragon soul, 10/16 hc msv,hof,toes, 8/12 hc tot, 11/14 mythic soo, 1/7 hm and that's where all stops since i took a break and came back now ready to raid ( 9/10 hc brf with group finder ).
Mindset (describe your attitude on progress and farm raids):I like to play wow, been playing for almost 6 years and been raiding for 4 years. My attitude is very simple, whenever the raid time starts, i focus until it ends.
Combatlog links: My HM logs expired and i don't have brf logs because i had been pugging.
Screenshot of your UI while raiding (use Imgur):http://imgur.com/6WbLFmT
Which important addons and WAs do you use?BigWigs for raidin ( obviously );
ExtraCD for my ring and trinket proc;
TidyPlates for my weapon enchant and flame shock dot;
Skada for evaluating my dps/damage taken
Which macros do you use?I use macros that combine 2 spells ( using shift between them ) to clear my action bars and one burst macro where i combine Ascendance and Elemental Mastery;
Which keybinds do you use?Q E V F G X Z Y CNTRL X CNTRL Q CNTRL E CNTRL V CNTRL G
Explain your talent and glyph choices and alternatives:My talents and glyphs had been chosen in order to maximize my dps by inspecting logs and guides on the internet.
How do you check what your dps is like?Skada
Where do you find new info about your class?noxxic.com and icyveins.com
If you have geared alts, at which lvl can you play them?I don't even have max level alts
Do you know anyone from the guild?I don't think so.
Previous guilds
Which guilds and roles?
My current guild is The fugitives which i joined 3 weeks ago to raid, but right a day after i joined, the GM which is also the RL had an IRL accident and took a break, which meant the disbandment of the guild. Until then i was in Behemoth, a guild i joined in december 2012 and in which i had been a loyal raider, until everyone just suddenly quitted the game and it had to disband. My roles were the same since i play only this shaman.
Anything else you wanna add?

I am a student at a Computer Science faculty, i suck at literature so I appologize if my answeres weren't as you expect. What i can guarantee is that i am an active raider that just happened to log on without a guild. I may not have current raiding experience, but my experience as a raider is there, and trust me, i have many. All I need is a chance to prove myself and you will not be dissapointed.

fields.body_html:
Summary and comparison time

Our first log

And our Kill with tries

Kill is a kill and let's take it for granted. But still hefty amount of things can be upgraded to make future kills smoother.

Pros
Overall dps was better *2.33b vs 2.03*
Same goes for healing 961kk vs 817kk
Tact change that fits the raiders. * finally ^^ *
Active time boost for some people.

Cons
Sometimes stacking doesn't go well and raid ends up with too many smart stamps
Pulvy phase is shorter due to BL but it killed us way more then it had on our first try. *without reseting it would go way over 300*
Survive/Active time wasn't much of a change from the first try we had and its still far from perfect.

fields.body_html:
About yourself

First name: Liselot, but you can just call me Liv
Age: 19
Gender: Female
Country: Netherlands

Your computer

System specifications:
processor: Intel® Core™ i7-4790K Processor
(8M Cache, up to 4.40 GHz)
graphics: SAPPHIRE TRI-X R9 290X 4GB GDDR5 OC (UEFI)
operating system: Windows® 7 Home Premium 64-bit
ram: Dominator® with DHX Pro Connector 8GB Dual Channel DDR3
hard drive: HyperX 3K

FPS during general raiding:
>60 fps steady

FPS during raiding and heavy load (bloodlust+spam everything+shiny boss abilities):
>60 fps steady

Do you have and use a microphone?
That can be arranged if its required.

Internet connection (use speedtest, pick Paris which is where the Draenor server is located, and paste the result-URL):
http://www.speedtest.net/my-result/4403940028

How often do you disconnect?
Only when there are server problems.

How often does your PC crash?
Never

Character information

Character name: Livh
Class: Hunter
Spec: Survival
Amory link: http://eu.battle.net/wow/en/character/draenor/Livh/advanced
Off-spec (if any) : Beastmastery
Alts worth mentioning:
http://eu.battle.net/wow/en/character/draenor/Tsuruhime/advanced

Raiding

Raiding schedule and IRL (will our raiding schedule fit your real life?):
It should always be able to fit.

Previous expansion experience:
Joined late pandaria, so did not have a lot of chance to raid to full extent

Mindset (describe your attitude on progress and farm raids):
If the people are all there, and its all ready to go i'm always ready to raid. Even though farm content might get boring, i still look at it as an opportunity to improve personally, and maybe help other guildies.

Combatlog links:
https://www.warcraftlogs.com/reports/fd1QGgvTVchNRPxa#
some logs from Beastlord Mythic

Screenshot of your UI while raiding (use Imgur):
http://i.imgur.com/Z6Tb3rE.jpg
note: its a screenshot from my laptop (hence the odd resolution), if you want the definitive version, give me a shout!

Which important addons and WAs do you use?
addons i use:
-Vuhdo
-SUF
-Bigwigs
-Bartender4
-Chatter
-Quartz
-Skada (healing, damage, and threat)
-Gladius (pvp)
(also Angry Assignments, Weakaura's for some bosses, and Exorsus raid tools)

Which macros do you use?
none

Which keybinds do you use?
keybinds are quit simple, use most frequent spells on 1/6, and f1/f5, others i put on shiftbinds (my hands are not that big, so a lot is out of reach).
Also a few on Z, X, C, F, G, R.
And some mouse binds (steelseries sensei)

Explain your talent and glyph choices and alternatives:
< = default choice,
- = optional choice
made for survival spec
15
Posthaste < The mobility has always been handy
Narrow Escape
Crouching Tiger, Hidden Chimaera - Fights where disengage and deterrence is needed more often then usual
30
Binding Shot < Since i dont use a pet to Intimidate with, most logical choice
Wyvern Sting -
Intimidation
45
Exhilaration < Its controllable, which makes me find it more reliable then the other choices
Iron Hawk -
Spirit Bond
60
Steady Focus < Easy in use, guaranteed buff
Dire Beast
Thrill of the Hunt- comes in handy on aoe fights (multishots)
75
A Murder of Crows < Short CD, powerfull spell
Blink Strikes
Stampede - Stampede has been bugged for me ever since WoD started. It will only call out 2 pets, under any circumstances
90
Glaive Toss < Single target
Powershot
Barrage < AoE
100
Exotic Munitions- PvP
Focusing Shot
Lone wolf< Buffs can come in handy, and from the tests i've performed i just get highest dps with it

How do you check what your dps is like?
Skada, Warcraftlogs and ask mr robot's logs

Where do you find new info about your class?
forums, chatting around, patchnotes

If you have geared alts, at which lvl can you play them?
I have a fully hc geared Mistweaver/Brewmaster monk. Cleared BRF hc, beastlord myth,
progressed on hans, ore and gruul.

Do you know anyone from the guild?
not as far as i know! Talked to Dotftw for a bit tho.

Previous guilds
Which guilds and roles?
Hellscream and Inhumane- draenor as raider (dps and healer)
Borderpatroll-TarrenMill as Raider (healer) (current guild on healer)

Anything else you wanna add?
Have been focussing on my healer for the last few weeks. But the guild it's in, has been showing problems. There is not enough commitment along the raiders. 3 raids a week are planned, and for the last 2 weeks, only 1 raid went on. They tried pugging players for mythic. But that did not work out too well.
Suggested many alternatives, but there is no ear for that.
Because i want to keep my personal progress going, i am looking to expand my options in other places. What i really want, is a steady guild, that could offer me better progress and ''experience'' then i am getting now.

fields.body_html:
My thought is that this rank can be obtained by everybody. The whole raid can even be in it.

But we might get into problems with our ongoing benching of sub average players vs the rest of the group. One player that is well above average now might be sub average in some months when the rest of the group has caught up or been replaced with better.

If the idea should work the rank has to be fluid, and not permanent for each player. But "suddenly" demoting the same player for no longer being "good enough" might not be well taken.



The idea was to give some kind of carrot to those who are behaving well and giving more to the raid than they get. It's also what we want all the raiders to be like, so maybe they don't need any carrot to be what they are supposed to be?

I was just thinking of boosting ppl's motivation. Maybe it should be done in another way.

Maybe "veteran raider" is better after all, since it can mean something like "permanent raid spot" and not any huge chance for being benched like most new ppl are. Then again we won't get that fluidity when the raid as a whole improves. Hmm…



Maybe we rather should do something like creating boost runs in one of our scheduled raid rays when we have cleared the content (in the future) and split the boosting cash between all the raid members. Pick those who "deserve" that money. In heroic Will be like 20-40k+ per person in a fairly new instance if we boost one person per armor class. More if we do it on mythic. Boosting full mythic with gear is like 750k gold for one person.



Anyways, "perks" can come in many forms. Doesn't have to be anything mentioned so far.

Template for email application:
About yourself

First name:
Tilen

Age:
18

Gender:
Male

Country:
Slovenia
Your computer

System specifications:
Intel Core i7-4702MQ 3.2GHz
NVIDIA GeForce GT750M
8GB DDR3 memory
500GB HDD
*Soon going to replace my computer for a new rig*

FPS during general raiding:
Got FPS locked to 45 while raiding. Having it at 60FPS would make my laptop overheat in the current temperatures (~30celsius)

FPS during raiding and heavy load (bloodlust+spam everything+shiny boss abilities):
45FPS
Do you have and use a microphone?
Yes have logitech G430
Internet connection (use speedtest, pick Paris which is where the Draenor server is located, and paste the result-URL):
http://www.speedtest.net/my-result/4420963860

How often do you disconnect?
Rarely, once 1-2 a week.

How often does your PC crash?
Under normal circumstances almost never.
Character information

Character name:
Zulvin

Class:
Druid

Spec:
Feral

Amory link:
http://eu.battle.net/wow/en/character/draenor/Zulvin/simple
Off-spec (if any):
Restoration
Alts worth mentioning:
None, but I have a lot of expirience as restoration and 695IL set.
Raiding

Raiding schedule and IRL (will our raiding schedule fit your real life?):
Yes
Previous expansion experience:
I have been casual/focusing on PVP for most of my WoW "career". Done some progression raiding in Catacylsm. I have been extremely casual in MoP.
In WoD I wanted to partake in serious progression which worked fine at the start. Done 2/7M in january but the guild broke apart.
I decided to stay with the guild since I got attached to some members but the progression was really slow. Usually not progressing at all for weeks.(Not even on a 1 fight scale)
got to 2/10M before april. Eventually many members left and the guild broke apart again. Since my exams were in april may and june I decided to take a 2 month break.
Mindset (describe your attitude on progress and farm raids):
I clearly understand that a important part of progression means wiping. I am a calm person and usually don't tilt. I am prepared to give a 100% from the first minute to last until the raid leader calls it a night. I find farm raids important since it helps everybody get their missing items which helps the guild in the long run.

Combatlog links:
I've been restoration for most of WoD so I don't have any relevant feral combatlogs. If you are interested I can try to find my restoration combat logs from mythic oregorger progression.

Screenshot of your UI while raiding (use Imgur):
http://i.imgur.com/qYmldkg.jpg
I know it looks clunky but that's how I had it for almost 2 years and got used to it.
Which important addons and WAs do you use?
For Raidingeadly Boss Mods, Bartender 4, OmniCC, Skada, TargetHealthPercent,Thogar assists
My last weak auras profile got deleted so I have to make a new one. but I will soon add weak auras to the list.
Which macros do you use?
I use my useform/cancelform macros, my cooldown burst macro on all boss fights. I usually make new macros for bosses where it is necessary.
Which keybinds do you use?
I have my core rotation and cooldowns keybinded. Some things I don't use keybinds for: buffs,normal revive(Not CR) and abilities which are extremely situational.
I use logitech G600
Explain your talent and glyph choices and alternatives:
Displacer Beast - Helps to stick on the target and also serves as a blink to get out of danger.
Ysera's Gift - Outheals the other two options plus it's a passive.
mass Entanglement- very situational tier, going to change it if it proves useful to a boss fight
Incarnation: King of the Jungle - Strongest pick damage wise. Soul of the forest is passive but clearly a DPS loss.
Ursol's Vortex - Again a situational tier but ursol vortexs is in most cases the most useful one
Dream of Cenarius - Since I use Blood Talons healing wave is a part of my rotation so Dream of Cenarius clearly enhances the healing of the ability and let's me control who am I about to heal.
Blood talons -Strongest pick out of the 3. While Lunar inspiration may be a tiny DPs increase in "council" fights, blood talons also increases your survivability by making healing touch a high priority spell.
Glyphs:
Glyph of cat - It's a base 20% healing taken increase. Very solid.
Glyph of Savage Roar - the only glpyh which is a DPs increase. Allows me to get a free savage roar at the beginning of the fight
Glyph of Rebirth - My combat ress now ressurects the person with 100% health.

How do you check what your dps is like?
I generally use SKADA as my DPS meter.
Where do you find new info about your class?
Icy veins has basic guides, but from time to time there are great indepth posts on the official forums.

If you have geared alts, at which lvl can you play them?
I have a ~680 IL enhancement shaman. I can play him but I don't like the current state of enhancement shamans in PVE.

Do you know anyone from the guild?
Not yet but I hope to get to know some great people
Why should we pick you?
I am free from school for the next 3 months which allows me to dedicate my time to raiding. I am prepared to take the extra step to be competitive and help the guild as a whole. I am a calm person and always try to stay out of drama. I also accept criticism and always try to improve. I have good knowledge of many specs. I am also a social person and quickly get used to people. I also have a lot of experience as restoration and am ok with going resto if you might lack a healer one night.
Previous guilds

Which guilds and roles?
Habits - Evade
After Habits split I have been a founding member and healing officer of Evade.
Anything else you wanna add?
I know I might be a gamble since I haven't done a lot of raiding as feral in this expansions, but I've always played feral and don't think it will take a lot of time to get on a competitive level. I hope you take me into consideration.
