Dream of Cenarius - Since I use Blood Talons healing wave is a part of my rotation so Dream of Cenarius clearly enhances the healing of the ability and let's me control who am I about to heal.
Blood talons -Strongest pick out of the 3. While Lunar inspiration may be a tiny DPs increase in "council"  fights, blood talons also increases your survivability by making healing touch a high priority spell.
Glyphs:
Glyph of cat - It's a base 20% healing taken increase. Very solid.
Glyph of Savage Roar - the only glpyh which is a DPs increase. Allows me to get a free savage roar at the beginning of the fight
Glyph of Rebirth - My combat ress now ressurects the person with 100% health.

[color="green"]How do you check what your dps is like?[/color]
I generally use SKADA as my DPS meter.
[color="green"]Where do you find new info about your class?[/color]
Icy veins has basic guides, but from time to time there are great indepth posts on the official forums.

[color="green"]If you have geared alts, at which lvl can you play them?[/color]
I have a ~680 IL enhancement shaman. I can play him but I don't like the current state of enhancement shamans in PVE.

[color="green"]Do you know anyone from the guild?[/color]
Not yet but I hope to get to know some great people ;)
[b][size=5]Why should we pick you?[/size][/b]
I am free from school for the next 3 months which allows me to dedicate my time to raiding. I am prepared to take the extra step to be competitive and help the guild as a whole. I am a calm person and always try to stay out of drama. I also accept criticism and always try to improve. I have good knowledge of many specs. I am also a social person and quickly get used to people. I also have a lot of experience as restoration and am ok with going resto if you might lack a healer one night.
[b][size=5]Previous guilds[/size][/b]

[color="green"]Which guilds and roles?[/color]
Habits - Evade
After Habits split I have been a founding member and healing officer of Evade.
[b][size=5]Anything else you wanna add?[/size][/b]
I know I might be a gamble since I haven't done a lot of raiding as feral in this expansions, but I've always played feral and don't think it will take a lot of time to get on a competitive level. I hope you take me into consideration.

If anyone asks, whether it's a possible applicant, a trialist, a member, anyone, the trial length is as long as each trialist needs. It's up to each person how long it will be.


If trialists ask if their trial period is over soon we add 2 raid days to that person's trial period. One simply don't ask for that. It's over when the officers say it's over.



Default trial lengths:
1 week for x-members who come back from slacking.
3 weeks as standard
2 weeks as exception if we know the person well
4-5 weeks if lower ilvl and progression
6+ weeks usually means failed trial. (Demote to "slacker" and let them /gquit if they want.)

fields.body:
[b]If anyone asks[/b], whether it's a possible applicant, a trialist, a member, anyone, [b]the trial length is as long as each trialist needs[/b]. It's up to each person how long it will be.


If trialists ask if their trial period is over soon we add 2 raid days to that person's trial period. One simply don't ask for that. It's over when the officers say it's over.



[u][b]Default trial lengths:[/b][/u]
1 week for x-members who come back from slacking.	
3 weeks as standard	
2 weeks as exception if we know the person well	
4-5 weeks if lower ilvl and progression	
6+ weeks usually means failed trial. (Demote to "slacker" and let them /gquit if they want.)

The first and the last boss drop a caster staff. We farm the first boss, but we will never kill the last one. The staff from the last boss is BiS for mages since it has better secondary stats.
We kill the first boss, and the staff drops. Mages A and B have the same staff currently equipped. Mage A clicks 'Upgrade' on the loot council addon, mage B clicks 'BiS upgrade'.

Which mage clicked the right button?

Bolts vs Pajack…


I'd say they should still click "BiS" and "upgrade" based on the gear that is BiS, no matter if it's available or not. Then we keep that in mind and see who will give more to the raid group in terms of dps, and then increased dps from that weapon.


These numbers are made up, and only meant as illustration:


Raidmember1 does 40k dps and has weapon1 as BiS.
Raidmember2 does 50k dps and has weapon2 as BiS.

Weapon 1 SHOULD give raidmember1 4k more dps, but because of skillcap it only gives 2k more dps.
Weapon 2 SHOULD give raidmember1 3k more dps, but because of skillcap it only gives 1,5k more dps.

Weapon 1 gives raidmember2 3k more dps since he has higher skillcap.
Weapon 2 gives raidmember2 4k more dps since he has higher skillcap.

The raidgroup as a whole gets 1k dps MORE if we give a non-BiS to a better dps.





Raidmember3 has higher skillcap, but not as high as raidmember2.

Weapon 1 SHOULD give raidmember1 4k more dps, but because of skillcap it only gives 3k more dps.

The raidgroup as a whole now doesn't gain any dps if we give a non-BiS to a better dps.

Weapon 1 gives raidmember2 3k more dps since he has higher skillcap.
Weapon 2 gives raidmember2 4k more dps since he has higher skillcap.

The raidgroup as a whole gets 1k dps MORE if we give a non-BiS to a better dps.





Raidmember3 has higher skillcap, but not as high as raidmember2.

Weapon 1 SHOULD give raidmember1 4k more dps, but because of skillcap it only gives 3k more dps.

The raidgroup as a whole now doesn't gain any dps if we give a non-BiS to a better dps.

After enough trouble with Zverko we talked in /o about maybe it's time to let Zverko go. With Knof going mostly boomkin atm we would then be down to 4 healers when Curumon goes afk (in a month++). The thought that popped up then was to ask if Zulvin would like to heal "instead" of dps as feral, but go feral when we have too many healers on a day. A little sucky to be too many healers for a month, but we need some reliable soon anyways. And this guy has good numbers on warcraftlogs + he was healer officer in the previous guild.

I /w with him today with Bishi on TS. Zulvin likes and accepts the idea. He also says his feral dps is increasing but not quite yet up to par on ppl who have long xp on it. But he will do his best and keep progress so he can use it when we need it.

Zulvin will come on wednesday in Hellfire Citadel as healer.

It's Excel file with pivot table. If you don't have M$ Excel atm you can download a "free" version of Office 2013 here:

(File is named 1234test.rar to bypass Google's autocheck routines.)


Click to download WinRAR 3.4 if you need it.



Most important thing with the Excel file is to get familiar with the stat weights when voting for who gets which loot. Some ppl might not be up to date on 6.2 and might click BiS for something that isn't bis for them.

I wanted to add which class+spec that has each item as BiS in the pivot table, so we could just search for an item and see who should get it, but it turned out to be too much work since some good set items can be switched out for even better regular drop items. I can add all the BiS'es for all the items later when I get my hands on BiS lists for the classes. When I update the Excel file you have to download it again. I'll let you know.

Which items who want need to be pushed onto each member. They should know this themselves. This is something that is required for all who want to do the harder bosses on mythic.

Don't die > do everything right > dps

Close your Skada/Recount. Do not watch it during progress!

If someone have low dps on certain targets the officers will tell them about it, and it will be fixed one way or the other.

Otherwise your dps ranking is irrelevant as long as the bosses die.

fields.body_html:
Now that Blizz has done the first wave of emergency class balancing the stat weights and which items are BiS is stabilizing. With that we can do our summarizing with Google Sheets so we get a clear picture of which class+spec need which items.

https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1P_a1LU2TCtMFZDOm628pt6pdG07c-4obgYmUA9hxFQY/edit


Go to the sheet for your class and below the table there write the BiS items for your spec. Write something like: itemname+boss+slot (finger/neck/legs/etc)+your spec. The sheet "Item list" to the left containts all items that drop in Hellfire Citadel, and list them by item names, which boss they drop from, ilvl, which stats, etc. Figure out which items are BiS for you (including which set item you sacrifice for even better regular drop) and copy the itemname+boss to your class sheet. You can even copy whatever you found somewhere on the internet as long as it's up to date, and paste them in the class sheet.



As alternativ for working in Google Sheets (and it's lack of pivot tables) you can download this Excel file, fill in your info, and when you're done send it to afkish@gmail.com. The Excel file has pivot table which makes it much, much easier to filter the table to only show leather+agi, etc. If you don't have M$ Office you can download a "free" version of Office 2013 here (the file is named 1234test.rar to bypass Google's autocheck routines.), and WinRAR here.




Blizz might still do some more changes in the future. Keep an eye out for changes that affect you.

Hi, hi since the eye management wasn't going as expected here is some help. Now we have 2 ways of dealing with it.
First is… Old fashion way *Create macro !*

Macro:
/target [@mouseover]
/click ExtraActionButton1
/targetlasttarget

This should be enough to instantly throw dat EYE.

And here's the new way. the "ez" way, the one that everyone will chose.

ERT which we used for Kromie hands placement

Aaaand here's something that only focuses on Iskar and his little eye

IA

Of course you still need to know when to throw and what to do.

Regards from the lone monk

Do you know you can go Dragon roar for every single fight in the instance and get the same dmg or more? Anger management is right however when would you switch to ravager? Also do you know how to utilise AM? Such as knowing when the use the shortened recklessness to have it back for executes? This is a long reply i know, but if its one thing i know about - Its warriors.

I've watched it before and I gotta say the tank that does the construct isn't even close to maximize the usage of it. And the easiest way of dealing with this boss even after the buffs is to finish him before reentering the phase 1. As for how to do that is all about the construct so setting everything before and once the domi comes nuke him with the robot. Ideally would be to deal at least 50% damage on him by the robot himself.
As for the casters there should be an interrupt list/duty. On our runs we had to dispel more with only 1 phase then they did with 2. No need to add that it wrecks mana and no mana = no healing = wipe. ^^

fields.body_html:
Reverberating Blow:

Inflicts 92500 to 107500 Physical damage to all targets in a cone. Additionally, applies 3 stacks of Shattered Defenses, dividing the number of stacks between the closest targets.



So it's possible to abuse melees on this, to soak one of the 3 stacks, so that the tank won't reach extreme amount of stacks and almost die all the time. If all the melees (wow, we have so many of them!) ninja soak one blow (blow the boss or the tank?) each in turns the tank would get an easier time surviving P1.

fields.body_html:
For some reason this boss went from being a pushover to let's say 2nd hardest boss in HFC. Tanks die to melee because we're doing the transition to p1 when everyone or at least most of the people are moving and they sometimes end up without any healing *out of range* and on top of that the targets that have gift by the time we get to the place are nearly dead especially if they get the debuff from the construct. So for clearing that we could do as we did the last few tries and just stay stacked on the portal and tanks get the mech to middle of the room while range clear the ghosts.

But honestly we should just do it without transition just like that guild it the link above. The dps check for domie isn't that big and we have the people who can burst those down fast plus we're gonna get some new gear on tomorrows run. With 4 doms out only 3 of them are dangerous 1-2-4 because the 3rd one overlaps with apocalypse so it's basically no dmg to construct. As for the mech to do that priority list is. 2-3 fire lanes and just nuke boss -> domi we can even skip the prisons with our aoe team but can be done either way.

About yourself
First name: Daniel

Age: 25

Gender: Male

Country: Denmark
Your computer

System specifications:
Processor: Intel(r) Core(TM) I7-3820 CPU @ 3.60GHz 3.60 GHz
Ram: 16Gb
Grafik card: AMD Radeon HD 7900 HD Series

FPS during general raiding: 30-40

FPS during raiding and heavy load (bloodlust+spam everything+shiny boss abilities): 30-40

Do you have and use a microphone? Yeah i do.

Internet connection speedtest:

How often do you disconnect? Never, or actually nah forget it never DCed where it was on my end, but on Blizzards end quite a few times when going to garrison.

How often does your PC crash? In wow Never.
Character information

Character name: Ogura

Class: Warrior

Spec: M: Furry , O: Prot

Amory link (log out with the gear you are applying with): http://eu.battle.net/wow/en/character/draenor/Ogura/simple

Off-spec (if any): Prot

Alts worth mentioning (with links): got a 100 of everything expect Paladin and DK, where my lock is 692 Ilvl but got bored of lock so started playing warrior instead when 6.2 did hit.
Raiding

Raiding schedule and IRL (will our raiding schedule fit your real life?): Everyday fits me, and Anytime as long as its not dinner time

Previous expansion experience: 10/13 HFC Norm, 10/10 BRF HC, 7/7 HM Hc

Mindset (describe your attitude on progress and farm raids): I don't mind endless dying as long as its just same stupid thing people fail on everytime, (Ex. moving from Barrage on iron reaver)

Combatlog links: Got no log, since the guild i been in did not do logs so got none to share.

Screenshot of your UI while raiding Tinypic // Tinypic)):

Which important addons and WAs do you use?
i use ElvUI, DBM, GTFO, ExtraCD, Skada Damage Meter,

Which macros do you use?
#showtooltip Recklessness
/cast Blood Fury(Racial)
/cast Bloodbath
/cast Recklessness
/cast Berserker Rage
/use 13
/use 14

—

#showtooltip Charge
/cast [harm] Charge; [help] Intervene

—

#showtooltip
/cast Shield Wall
/cast Last Stand
/cast Rallying Cry
/cast Enraged Regeneration
/cast Skull Banner
/use 13
/use 14

—

#showtooltip
/cast Rallying Cry
/cast Enraged Regeneration

Which keybinds do you use? F, R, T, G, H, Mousewheel up/down, Mousebutton 4/3, Shift+Space, Ctrl+Space

Explain your talent and glyph choices and alternatives:

Glyphes:
Enraged Speed - +20% Movement speed when enraged, which you basically is all the time in combat, which makes you able to evade stuff faster or get into position faster.

Unending Rage - +20 max Rage enough said.
Rude Interruption - When interrupting gives +6% bonus Damage for 20secs meaning more damage while doing your job?.

Talents and Why:

Row 1: Double Time, gives 1 extra charge so it can hold 2 charges whats not to love.
Row 2: Enraged Regeneration Vs Impending Victory
They basically heals the same amount, Enraged just dont use rage which you use for your combat abilities where impending victory uses 10 rage.

Row 3: Sudden Death, gives my Auto attacks a chance to make me able to use Execute no matter the hp of the boss, gives a massive dps boost and other talents on that line cant match it.

Row 4: Storm Bolt Vs Shockwave Vs Dragon Roar
Storm Bolt can only be used against 1 target and if there is at any time chance you can hit more then one it is worse then the other two.

Shockwave is only good if you need a stun, which is useless in raid since you cant stun anything with it.

Dragon Roar is the top dps one of these with 1min Cd, and aoe and 100% crit chance which makes it even better then storm bolt at single target, they are only around 300dps from each other on single target so no biggie.

Row 5: Mass Spell Reflection Vs Vigilance
Mass Spell Reflection: is okay if you know for sure there will be aoe spell that can be counter, (which never happens in raid)

Vigilance gives you a reduce damage skill you can use on the tanks to make em take less damage when there is a large hit on its way like Acid torrent.

Row 6: Bladestorm Vs Bloodbath
Bloodbath does look good on paper but in total it does same damage as bladestorm in total, where bladestorm also can crit while bloodbath can't.

So overall Bladestorm is better for single target and multitarget.

Row 7: Anger Management Vs Ravager Vs Siegebreaker

This row is fun, Anger management wants you to actually use your Rage ALOT, to reduce cooldown on all your damage boosting abilities like Recklessness.

Ravager is just a throw on the ground hope enemy dont move aoe damage, that does rather low damage and Anger management makes you able to do more damage then this by making you able to throw in a few more bladestorms if your good at using it.

Siegebreaker is just a single blow to the head of the enemy with quite a large amount of damage but too long cooldown compared to what it does.

How do you check what your dps is like?
Skada Dps Meter.

Where do you find new info about your class?
Icy-veins, AskmrRobot

If you have geared alts, at which lvl can you play them?
Warlock quite well 10/10 Hc BRF with it.

Do you know anyone from the guild?
Nope none yet, but hopefully will get to.

Previous guilds
Reboot.

Which guilds, roles and why did you leave?
Reboot, got kicked cause i had to drive my mom to the hospital when raid started.

Where did you hear about us?
Life whispered me cause he had seen my spam in trade chat.

Why should we pick you?
Cause a Fury warrior that always comes to the raid is not that bad is it?

Anything else you wanna add?
I basically never stays away from a raid unless im about to die.

fields.body_html:
Since FreeLoot will presumably die today, it's a good time to learn the next boss that we will face. Here's a quick summary of how to Xhul 1 min max of reading
Just like in maidens there isn't anything hard that's going on before 35% and then 20%. The whole fight is around this. Run>Stack>Cleave repeat and then the 20% which is a soft dps check because the OC will grow stronger every 10s.

Watching fatboss etc is really nice but for learning i think it's better to see how other guild from our server did "Kill" here's some logs of guilds with similar Ilvl

First: 7 min kill This one involves killing the Unstable adds asap
Second: 5 min kill This is more oriented at dodging Unstable for as much as u can and focusing the boss.
